So I'd tweet sm info abt #HALITOSIS ... Origin, Causes, Pathogenesis, diagnosis, treatment. Hope we all get to learn a lil about it.
The Social Turn off... A Medical issue of sorts... #Halitosis
1) The mouth is home to hundreds of bacterial species with various nutritional preferences... #Halitosis
2) Oral malodor is primarily the result of microbial metabolism... These microbes digest proteins leading to bad breath #Halitosis
3) Halitosis can be an important social problem in which the "standard" mouthwashes can provide only temporary relief... #Halitosis
4) Statistically, studies have shown that Bad breath is prevalent in about 2.2-2.6% of the adult population. #Halitosis
5) Statistics aside, we all know bad breath could be quite common and is much of a social turn off as anything is. #Halitosis
6) Medically, let's look at the cause of #Halitosis.
7) The Main cause of bad breath, Is the presence of Volatile Sulfur compounds(VSCs) that produce these bacteria... #Halitosis
8) The bacteria colonise over the tongue and then digest proteins from food and in turn they produce several fetid substances... #Halitosis
9) VSC's could include methylmercaptan, hydrogen sulfite ... All found in the mouth #Halitosis
10) Having talked about the origin, let's look at the pathogenesis (how it happens) #Halitosis
11) First, In people who have good oral hygiene, good dentition and healthy gums the main cause of bad breath is... #Halitosis
12) From the back(deep part) of the tongue. They're likely to have deeply grooved tongues which could accumulate bacteria more #Halitosis
13) Such an accumulation would lead to low oxygen levels, and such "anerobic" conditions would let the bacteria thrive. #Halitosis
14) Second, Dentures (artificial teeth) is another cause of bad breath, esp if worn overnight. As the bacteria acc. During sleep #Halitosis
15) Third, Saliva plays a BIG role in #Halitosis. Bad breath levels during the day are inversely related to saliva flow. #Halitosis
16) When saliva flow is lowest (at night, after a fast, due to insufficient water intake, xerostomia, closed mouth for long) ... #Halitosis
17) That could cause an increase in the intensity of bad breath as there's static in the mouth, causing accumulation of bacteria #Halitosis
18) Conversely, chewing, concomitant cleansing of the oral cavity, movement of saliva, fluid intake could reduce bacteria levels #Halitosis
19) Clinical studies show that the bacteria found in those with fresh breath is found in 1 of 6 people with bad breath. #Halitosis
20) Contrary to what you might think, only very few cases of halitosis originate from outside the mouth (GIT, lungs, Nasal odor) #Halitosis
21) So how exactly is halitosis diagnosed/detected ... Cupping your hands over your mouth and mouth breathing into them is one. #Halitosis
22) The Intensity of Halitosis is based on the Rosenberg scale, which rates: 0- Not detected. 1- barely detectable. #Halitosis
23) Rosenberg scale contd. 2- Slight malodour. 3- Malodour definitely detected. 4- Strong malodour. 5- Very strong malodour. #Halitosis
24) The Rosenberg scale is based on measurement the amount of enzymes that contribute to the production of the fetide compounds. #Halitosis
#halitosis How to get rid of #BadBreath http://t.co/6SExWfkmXK
25) This is subjective, as it involves the doctor "smelling" the air from the patients mouth. So 2 docs are often used #Halitosis
26) Halimeters are also used to measure sulfur compound levels in the mouth and VSC probes too are used for intraoral diagnosis #Halitosis
28) Treatments for bad breath... There's a lot of them out there. #Halitosis
29) The best way to treat bad breath is to instill patients with good oral hygiene practices. #Halitosis
30) These practices include: brushing at least twice on a daily, oral cleansing after meals, agequate water intake, oral aeration #Halitosis
31) Dental floss usage significantly reduces bad breath too. Once there's adequate compliance from patients. #Halitosis
32) Mechanical ways of treating halitosis include: tongue brushing, tongue scraping, chewing gum with xylitol, oral hydration. #Halitosis
33) For the mouthwash users, they work best at night, as the active elements get to stay for longer periods in the mouth. #Halitosis
34) lastly, a change in diet could be required, if the halitosis is found to be frm a high VSC level from food intake. #Halitosis
35) There'll be a reduction in protein intake as most VSC's arise from the sulfur content of proteins. #Halitosis
